# Decision log

Time-ordered record of durable research-state transitions and commitments.
Do not use this file to narrate every experiment. Ordinary exploratory,
smoke-test, debugging, and non-load-bearing runs can live in a lightweight run
note, tracker run, notebook note, or results row.

## Format

```markdown
## YYYY-MM-DD — <short title>

- **Decision layer**: [project-level / workstream-level]
- **Workstream**: [project-level / workstreams/<name>]
- **Workstream label**: [N/A / R&D Workstream / Phenomenon / Mechanism Research]
- **Trigger**: [what observation, dependency, or user decision forced this entry]
- **State transition**:
  - [Q1/E2/C3/H4]: [active -> rejected / active -> merged / planned -> stale / ...]
- **Reason**: [specific evidence or design argument]
- **Alternatives considered**: [serious competing interpretation or action]
- **Next discriminating step**: [smallest next step, or "none; line closed"]
```

## Report provenance note

Use this only when a report package or external claim needs to tell a reviewer
how to resolve presented evidence. It is not a requirement for ordinary
research sessions or experiments.

```markdown
## YYYY-MM-DD — report provenance note

- **Decision layer**: [project-level / workstream-level]
- **Workstream**: [project-level / workstreams/<name>]
- **Workstream label**: [N/A / R&D Workstream / Phenomenon / Mechanism Research]
- **Report package**: [results/reports/RPT_<id>_<slug>/]
- **Presented evidence**: [figures, tables, artifact paths, tracker records, or rows]
- **Storage**: [local path, tracking URI, remote project, registry, or report provenance folder]
- **Lightweight run record**: [run note / tracker run / notebook note / results row pattern for ordinary exploration]
- **Presented evidence set**: [path or tracker query for cited evidence and selection/failed/sweep runs that affect this report claim]
- **Review retrieval**: [how a reviewer resolves evidence IDs to source artifacts]
- **Minimum provenance fields**: evidence ID, run ID or artifact URI, data version, git commit, environment pin, seed if relevant, params, headline metrics, rerun guidance
- **Reason**: [why this provenance path fits the report and collaboration model]
```

## Rules

- Record decisions that change what the project or workstream will or will not do.
- Record report provenance only when it changes how a reviewer resolves
  presented evidence.
- Record hypothesis deletion, merging, stale marking, and parking.
- Record R&D Workstream terminal decisions and Phenomenon / Mechanism Research
  promotion to `supported` only after the relevant workstream review path.
- Avoid vague decisions such as "try more models" or "need more data" unless
  they name the exact unblock condition.
- A decision entry is invalid if its only transition is `planned -> planned`,
  `none -> planned`, or "try / test / run X". Planning or narrating an ordinary
  experiment belongs in the run note, tracker run, trial notebook, results row,
  and the relevant workstream state object (`rd_plan.md` or
  `explanation_ledger.md`); `decisions.md` records pruning, merging, rejection,
  parking, support review, scope change, or durable commitment.
- User requests are not durable triggers by themselves. The trigger must name
  the evidence, dependency, contradiction, scope change, or state-compression
  reason that forced the decision.
